<item>
            <title>[HTTPCLIENT-1981] HttpTrace should not accept an entity</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HTTPCLIENT-1981</link>
                <project id="12310360" key="HTTPCLIENT">HttpComponents HttpClient</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The HttpTrace class allows a user to set an entity, but both RFC 2616 and RFC 7231 state that the client MUST NOT send an entity/message body. I&apos;ve attached a patch that throws an UnsupportedOperationException for trace requests in two places but maybe there is a better place/way to handle this.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
